default&#xa0;defaultThe UK Insurance Industry default&#xa0;defaultThe UK insurance industry is the third largest in the world and the largest in Europe. It is a 
defaultvital part of the UK economy, managing investments amounting to 26% of the UK’s total net worth and contributing £10.4 billion in taxes to the Government. Employing over 290,000 people in the UK alone, the insurance industry is also one of this country’s m
defaultajor exporters, with 28% of its net premium income coming from overseas business.
default&#xa0;
defaultInsurance helps individuals and businesses protect themselves against the everyday risks they face, enabling people to own homes, travel overseas, provide for a financially 
defaultsecure future and run businesses. Insurance underpins a healthy and prosperous society, enabling businesses and individuals to thrive, safe in the knowledge that problems can be handled and risks carefully managed. Every day, our members pay out £147 milli
defaulton in benefits to pensioners and long-term savers as well as £60 million in general insurance claims.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe ABIdefault&#xa0;
defaultThe Association of British Insurers (ABI) is the voice of insurance, representing the general insurance, protection, investment and long-term sa
defaultvings industry. It was formed in 1985 to represent the whole of the industry and today has over 300 members, accounting for some 90% of premiums in the UK.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe ABI’s role is to:
default• Be the voice of the UK insurance industry, leading debate and speaking up f
defaultor insurers.
default• Represent the UK insurance industry to government, regulators and policy makers in the 
default  
defaultUK, EU and internationally, driving effective public policy and regulation.
default• Advocate high standards of customer service within the industry and 
defaultprovide useful information to the public about insurance.
default• Promote the benefits of insurance to the government, regulators, policy makers and the public.
